bless dt and his aversion to macho posturing
summary:
Behind the Scenes of School Reunion (Part 6) 

Excerpts from Benjamin Cook’s interview with David Tennant about School Reunion...
caption:
Behind the Scenes of School Reunion (Part 6)

Excerpts from Benjamin Cook’s interview with David Tennant about School Reunion in DWM #370

DWM: Hello, David.  What was your worst subject at school?

David Tennant:  In terms of the one that I loathed, my worst subject was Maths, and related things like Physics. And Chemistry turned into Maths, which annoyed me enormously, cos I’d been quite enjoying Chemistry! But I wasn’t that bad at Maths particularly, I just hated doing it.  [Thinks] What was I actually bad at?  I didn’t flunk anything.

DWM: Were you much good on the sports field?

DT: Not particularly. I was in the rugby team very, very briefly, but only because I couldn’t get out of it! As soon as I could wriggle out of it, I did. I hated all that macho posturing nonsense that they love to do.

DWM: Were you well behaved at school?

DT: I remember complaining about things, and feeling very hard done by. I didn’t enjoy the process of having to go to school, because I didn’t want to be doing it, and it felt very wrong to me that I should be forced to go somewhere that I didn’t want to be.

DWM: Where did you want to be instead? Don’t tell me, run away and be an actor?

DT: Yeah, I did! [Laughs] I was precociously confident that that’s what I was going to do, therefore it was all a bit of a waste of time, because I was just marking time until I got to go to drama school at 17.  The very fact of childhood - not being allowed any responsibility - was one that annoyed me enormously. It felt very unfair.
